gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nets 124, Thunder 115
gameRecap.excerpt: Despite being outscored 68-49 in the second half, and 36-23 in the fourth quarter, the Nets held on to defeat the Thunder 124-115. Nic Claxton (23 points, 13 rebounds) and Spencer Dinwiddie (23 points, four assists) led the Nets as Cam Thomas added 19 points. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led the Thunder with his league leading twenty-fifth 30-point game with 34 points, nine rebounds, and six assists as Jalen Williams added 20 points, five rebounds, and five assists. The Nets snap a 5-game losing streak and improve to 16-20, as the Thunder move to 23-11.
